@startuml seq-toc
'' ============================================================================
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because: this flow has THREE distinct temporal phases
'' (extract on render, scroll-spy on every scroll, click-to-scroll) plus a
'' rAF self-message and re-entrant re-frame dispatches. PlantUML sequence gives
'' us `== phase ==` dividers, activation bars, `autonumber`, and self-messages
'' with per-participant lifeline coloring keyed to the concept palette — none of
'' which Mermaid sequence renders with stable per-actor color semantics.
'' ============================================================================
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Scroll-spy TOC — extract on render, spy on scroll, scroll on click

autonumber

participant "DataScript\n:doc/html"            as DS   #A45BAD
participant ":doc/toc sub\n(toc/extract)"        as SUB  #4F97D7
participant ".vv-toc panel\n(views/toc-panel)"   as PANEL #2D9574
participant ".vv-content\n(scroll container)"    as CONTENT #2D9574
participant "toc/spy!\n(renderer/toc)"           as SPY  #2D9574
participant "re-frame\nevent loop"               as RF   #4F97D7

== 1 · build the TOC (derived view, runs when rendered HTML changes) ==
DS  -> SUB   : :doc/html changes\n(:ds/rev bumps)
activate SUB
SUB -> SUB   : DOMParser.parseFromString(html)\nquerySelectorAll("h1..h6")\nkeep nodes with non-empty id\n→ [{:level :text :id}]
SUB --> PANEL : ordered headings (ids from rehype-slug)
deactivate SUB
PANEL -> PANEL : render <a.vv-toc-item .vv-toc-l{level}>\nper heading

== 2 · scroll-spy (rAF-throttled, on every content scroll) ==
CONTENT -> SPY : :on-scroll → toc/spy!(currentTarget)
activate SPY
SPY -> SPY : if spy-pending? → drop (coalesce)\nelse set spy-pending, requestAnimationFrame(…)
SPY -> SPY : **rAF tick**: ctop ≔ content.getBoundingClientRect().top\nfor each heading h:\n  if (h.top − ctop) ≤ 100px → active ≔ h.id\n  else → stop (keep last)
SPY -> RF : dispatch [:toc/active-heading active]
deactivate SPY
RF -> PANEL : :ui/active-heading updates →\nactive item gets .vv-toc-active\n(left border + head1 color)

== 3 · click a TOC entry → smooth-scroll the heading ==
PANEL -> RF : on-click → dispatch [:toc/goto id]
activate RF
RF -> RF : :toc/scroll fx\ngetElementById(id)
RF -> CONTENT : el.scrollIntoView({block:"start", behavior:"smooth"})
deactivate RF
note over CONTENT, SPY
  The smooth scroll re-fires :on-scroll, so phase 2 re-runs and the
  clicked heading naturally becomes the active highlight. **One source of
  truth** (the rendered headings); the active id is the only extra state.
end note

legend right
  |= color |= concept |
  | <#A45BAD> | DataScript SSOT (:doc/html) |
  | <#4F97D7> | re-frame machinery (sub / event loop) |
  | <#2D9574> | renderer (Chromium UI + DOM measurement) |
endlegend
@enduml
